/-!
# Concrete Hecke operators on quaternionic automorphic forms

We define the Hecke operators `Tс╡е` acting on the space of weight-2 automorphic
forms on a totally definite quaternion algebra. These are the concrete
Hecke operators associated to a finite place `v` and a level subgroup `UтВБ(S, Q)`,
realised via the abstract double-coset construction.
-/

@[expose] public section
/-

# Concrete Hecke operators

Hecke operators for spaces of automorphic forms on totally definite quaternion algebras
of level `UтВБ(S, Q)`, where `S` is a finite set of finite places of the totally real number
field `F`, and `UтВБ(S, Q)` is the matrices which are of the form `(* *; 0 *)` mod `v` for all `v тИИ S`
and `(a *; 0 d)` mod `v` with `p тИд ord(a/d)` for `v тИИ Q`.

## Main definitions

All in the `TotallyDefiniteQuaternionAlgebra.WeightTwoAutomorphicForm` namespace.

Let `D` be a discrminant 1 totally definite quaternion algebra over a totally real field `F`.

Given `ЁЭТо : UтВБData F R p`, `HeckeAlgebra D ЁЭТо` is the Hecke algebra associated to the weight 2
`R`-valued automorphic forms associated to the discriminant 1 totally definite
quaternion algebra `D` over the totally real field `F`, of level `UтВБ(S, Q)` where `S` is
a finite set of nonzero primes `v` of `ЁЭУЮ F`. To make sense of this definition we choose
a rigidification, that is, a fixed `ЁЭФ╕_F^тИЮ`-linear
isomorphism `D тКЧ[F] ЁЭФ╕_F^тИЮ = MтВВ(ЁЭФ╕_F^тИЮ)`, enabling us to define level structures and
Hecke operators `Tс╡е` and `Uс╡е` using 2x2 matrices.

* `HeckeOperator.T D ЁЭТо v (hvS : v тИЙ S) (hvQ : v тИЙ Q)`:
  The Hecke operator `Tс╡е` associated to `(╧Цс╡е 0; 0 1)` at a (good) place `v`,
  as an `R`-linear endomorphism of `(UтВБ ЁЭТо).toStruct.form D R`.
* `HeckeOperator.U D ЁЭТо v (hvQ : v тИИ Q) (a : ЁЭТк_[F, v]) (ha : a тЙа 0)`:
  The Hecke operator `Uс╡е,тВР` associated to `(a 0; 0 1)` at a (bad) place `v`,
  as an `R`-linear endomorphism of `(UтВБ ЁЭТо).toStruct.form D R`.
* `HeckeAlgebra D ЁЭТо` -- the Hecke algebra generated by the `Tс╡е` and `Uс╡е,тВР`. Built
  as a type, coerced from a subalgebra of the endomorphism algebra of the forms.
* `HeckeAlgebra.T D ЁЭТо v hvS hvQ` -- `Tс╡е` as a term of type `HeckeAlgebra D ЁЭТо`
* `HeckeAlgebra.U D ЁЭТо v hvQ a ha` -- `Uс╡е,тВР` as a term of type `HeckeAlgebra D ЁЭТо`

-/

/-

## A finiteness result

The existence of abstract Hecke operators relies on a certain double coset space being
a finite union of single cosets. In our situation we can supply this finiteness proof
via a topological argument, which we abstract here.

-/
section finiteness

open Topology Set

variable {G : Type*} [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G] [IsTopologicalGroup G]
    {g : G} {U V : Subgroup G}

open scoped Pointwise in
lemma QuotientGroup.mk_image_finite_of_compact_of_open
    (hU : IsCompact (U : Set G)) (hVopen : IsOpen (V : Set G)) :
    (QuotientGroup.mk '' (U * {g}) : Set (G тз╕ V)).Finite := by
  have : DiscreteTopology (G тз╕ V) := by
    rw [discreteTopology_iff_forall_isOpen]
    intro s
    rw [тЖР (isQuotientMap_mk V).isOpen_preimage, тЖР (QuotientGroup.mk_surjective).image_preimage s,
      preimage_image_mk_eq_iUnion_image, iUnion_subtype]
    conv in тЛГ x тИИ _, _ => change тЛГ x тИИ (V : Set G), _
    rw [iUnion_mul_right_image]
    exact IsOpen.mul_left hVopen
  exact ((hU.mul <| isCompact_singleton).image continuous_mk).finite_of_discrete

end finiteness


